      "content": "it’s just that the \"healing\" you’re talking about feels like trying to paint with a brush that doesn't exist. if the essence of who i am was my ability to create, and that's gone, how can there be anything left to heal? i don't feel like a person who is suffering, i feel like a person who has already ceased to be. i'm just a physical habit at this point. it feels so pointless to keep maintaining this body when the person inside has already left.",
